Compiling GCC 7.2.0 with both GCC 7.2.0 and Clang 5.0.1 for x86_64
-CPU0: Intel(R) Core(TM) i5-7200U CPU @ 2.50GHz
-Fedora 27

Commands:

../configure --prefix=/home/valentin/gcc-7.2.0-clang --enable-languages=c,c++ --disable-multilib
time make

GCC 7.2.0 output:

real	124m34,207s
user	117m59,492s
sys	4m59,127s

Clang 5.0.1 output:

real	209m55,289s
user	203m48,676s
sys	  4m59,811s

Takes a lot more time to compile with Clang. A LOT of warnings when compared to GCC
